<blockquote class="uncited"><div>Well....<br>je pense que je peux utiliser un petit peut francais mais je n'utilisait ca depuis... erm... deux mille huit je croix xD <br>Hardly rusty in it. Probably better in understanding than using it in which way ever... but well, happens <img class="smilies" src="https://www.emeraldimmersion.com/images/smilies/icon_e_biggrin.gif" width="15" height="17" alt=":D" title="Very Happy"></div></blockquote>Haha it's not that bad, as long as they understand what you're saying, French people ("normal" ones) will not get offended or mock you out... since many of them don't do better than you<br><br>Here is your correction :<br>"je pense que je peux utiliser un petit peut francais mais je n'utilisait ca depuis... erm... deux mille huit je croix xD"<br>"<span style="color:#FF0040">J</span><span style="color:#008040">e pense que je peux utiliser un petit </span><span style="color:#FF0040">peu de</span><span style="color:#008040"> français mais je n'</span><span style="color:#FF0040">utilises pas/je n'ai pas utilisé</span> <span style="color:#008040">ça depuis... erm... deux mille huit je </span><span style="color:#FF0040">crois</span> xD"<br><br>je n'utilises pas depuis &gt; Present "I don't use it since"<br>je n'ai pas utilisé depuis &gt; Past tense "I didn't used it since"<br>Or you wanted to say "i was using it in..." and there it's "je l'utilisais en ..."<br><br>See ? Not that bad, mainly orthography and conjugations problems but that's all ^^<br>PS : i'm a cheater, I use google translate everytime I have a doubt while typing my sentences<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://www.emeraldimmersion.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Yume</a> — Sat Apr 07, 2018 10:07 pm</p><hr />
